The Governor of Lagos State, Babajide Sanwo-Olu, has celebrated the impact of 100 women involved in the progressive development of the state by honouring them in a continued celebration of International Women’s Month. In a programme themed, ‘Eko Women 100’, the state said it identified and honoured women who are blazing the trail in their fields and contributing to the growth of the state while inspiring the next generation. In a statement, Sanwo-Olu said, “The Women of Lagos are powerful, visionary and represent our great state at the highest level globally.” This week we celebrated 100 of them in a project called #Eko100Women. These women have made Lagos their home bringing their expertise and excellence to great effect.” According to the statement, some of the women honoured include the First Lady of Lagos State, Dr Ibijoke Sanwo-Olu; Ibukun Awosika; Mo Abudu; Mrs Kofoworola Bucknor-Akerele; Fidelity Bank Managing Director, Nneka Onyeali-Ikpe; Managing Director, Guaranty Trust Holding Company Plc, Miriam Olusanya; Chief Executive Officer, North-West Petroleum, Winifred Akpani, and others.